#Basic Command of Linux : 
---------------------------

>>>clt + c => kill command 

>>>clt + z => stop (suspended) . run in the background .

>>>jobs => check the jobs number . 

>>>fg %jobs_number => which is running in the background . 

>>>clear => clear the content from terminal .

>>>exit => exit from terminal . 

---------------------------------------------------------
# check the host live or not (packet send or not ): 
-------------------------------------------------

>>> ping url_or_domainName => send the packet and check the host. 

>>> Tab => for auto complete the command . 

>>> cd => change the directory 

>>> cd . => current directory 

>>> cd .. => parent directory from current directory .

>>> pwd => show the current directory . 

>>> history => show the list of user command which already used . 

>>> clt + r => search the command history whiched alredy used in shell.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
terminal shortcut :
---------------------

>>> clt + a => Move cursor to the begining .

#before use the command use => clt+a , then use clt+k / clt+y

>>> clt + k => kill = Cut the line . 

>>> clt + y => yang = past . 

>>> clt + e => Move cursor to the end . 

>>> clt + l => clear the screen . 

>>> clt + r => search command already used in terminal.

--------------------------------------------------


